gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 118, Suns 110
gameRecap.excerpt: The Thunder defeated the Suns, 118-110. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander led the way for the Thunder with 35 points, eight rebounds and nine assists, his league-leading 45th 30+ point game of the season, while Jalen Williams added 22 points in the victory. Bradley Beal tallied 31 points and six assists for the Suns, while Jusuf Nurkic notched 14 points and a career-high 31 rebounds in the losing effort. The Thunder improve to 42-18 on the season, while the Suns fall to 35-26.
